<h3>Question 10</h3>
<div><p><p>How can you define function in PHP? Create a function that will take two integers as argument and will return product of them.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>Besides the built-in PHP functions, it is possible to create our own functions.</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>A function is a block of statements that can be used repeatedly in a program.</li>
<li>A function will not execute automatically when a page loads.</li>
<li>A function will be executed by a call to the function.</li>
</ul>
<p>To create function in PHP, We have start with function keyword followed by the function name.</p>
<p>The syntax for Function Define:</p>
<pre class="EnlighterJSRAW" data-enlighter-language="generic">function function_name( $parameters ){
    //custom code
}


/* While calling */
function_name(  $parameters  );</pre>
<p>Now, We make a function that will take two integers as arguments and will return the product of them.</p>
<div class="compilecode compilecode-php">
<pre class="EnlighterJSRAW" data-enlighter-language="generic">&lt;?php

function multiplytwonumber( int $num1, int $num2 ){
    return $num1 * $num2;
}

echo multiplytwonumber(5, 6);</pre>
<div class="compilecode-wrapper"><button type="button" class="compilecode-play">Run Code  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="13 17 18 12 13 7"></polyline><polyline points="6 17 11 12 6 7"></polyline></svg></button></div></div>
<p>The output of the above code is</p>
<pre class="EnlighterJSRAW" data-enlighter-language="generic">30</pre>
</div>
<h3>Question 11</h3>
<div><p><p>Describe CSS Box model with example.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>TheÂ <strong>CSS box model</strong>Â is a container that contains multiple properties including borders, margin, padding, and the content itself. It is used to create the design and layout of web pages. It can be used as a toolkit for customizing the layout of different elements. The web browser renders every element as a rectangular box according to the CSS box model.</p>
<p><img data-recalc-dims="1" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-10922 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/1_gq1B7v2_gDEi3jkAwAvZNQ.png?resize=1400%2C754&#038;ssl=1" alt="CSS Box Model" width="1400" height="754" /></p>
<p>Box-Model has multiple properties in CSS. Some of them are given below:</p>
<ul class="points">
<li><b>Content</b>Â &#8211; The content of the box, where text and images appear</li>
<li><b>Padding</b>Â &#8211; Clears an area around the content. The padding is transparent</li>
<li><b>Border</b>Â &#8211; A border that goes around the padding and content</li>
<li><b>Margin</b>Â &#8211; Clears an area outside the border. The margin is transparent</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Example:</strong></span></p>
<div class="compilecode compilecode-html">
<pre class="EnlighterJSRAW" data-enlighter-language="generic">div {
  width: 300px;
  border: 15px solid green;
  padding: 50px;
  margin: 20px;
}</pre>
